<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--PlaneCrash     05-21 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Plane Crash,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>2 Killed When Homemade Plane Plunges</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Planes Collide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NILES, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A homebuilt airplane crashed after
performing in an air show Sunday, killing its owner-pilot and a
passenger, authorities said.
   Charles E. White, 49, of Berrien Springs and James O. Billings
Jr., 45, of St. Joseph were pronounced dead at the scene of the
crash, said state police dispatcher Suzi Hibberd.
   The single-engine, two-seat plane built by White crashed at 3:06
p.m. in Howard Township, Hibberd said. Witnesses said the plane
made a sudden left turn and plummeted about 300 feet into a field.
   White and Billings had participated earlier Sunday in an air
show in Benton Harbor.
   The Federal Aviation Administration was investigating the cause
of the crash, Hibberd said.
</TEXT>
