<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Iran-Executions     05-21 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Iran-Executions,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fourteen Drug Traffickers Hanged</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fourteen drug traffickers convicted by
Islamic courts were hanged in two Iranian cities Sunday, raising
the number of such executions since January to 637, Tehran radio
reported.
   The broadcast, monitored in Nicosia, said the hangings took
place in northwestern Lahijan and central Birjand.
   In January, Iranian authorities launched a nationwide crackdown
on drug abuse. Under a new law, anyone caught in possession of even
small amounts of any drug receives the death penalty.
   In the last nine days alone, 79 drug traffickers were hanged.
   The government has said that about 1 million of Iran's 50
million people are drug abusers, but unofficial estimates put the
figure at twice that.
</TEXT>
