<FIRST>r a AM-People-Keith     05-21 0205</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Keith,0212</SECOND>
<HEAD>Star of Oliver North TV Miniseries Arrested For Alleged Drunken Driving</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST HOLLYWOOD, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   David Keith, the actor who played
former Lt. Col. Oliver North in the TV miniseries ``Guts and
Glory,'' was arrested for alleged felony drunken driving after
hitting another car, authorities said.
   Keith, 35, was allegedly speeding at about midnight Saturday
when he rammed a car making a U-turn, injuring a woman riding in
the other car, Los Angeles County sheriff's Deputy George
Ducoulombier said Sunday.
   The woman, whose name wasn't released, was treated at
Cedars-Sinai Medical Center for neck pain, Ducoulombier said. Her
condition wasn't available Sunday.
   ``He was charged with the more serious felony violation because
of the speeding and the injury,'' the deputy said.
   Keith's blood alcohol level was tested at more than .18 percent,
he said. The standard blood alcohol level defining drunken driving
is .10 percent.
   Keith was driving a 1988 Ford Mustang and hit a 1988 BMW,
Ducoulombier said. Keith, the driver of the BMW and an unidentified
woman traveling with the actor were uninjured.
   He was freed early Sunday morning after posting $2,500 bail, the
deputy said.
   Keith's film credits include ``An Officer and A Gentleman'' and
``Lords of Discipline.''
