<TEXT>
   An elevator fell from the
seventh floor of a hospital Sunday, killing all seven people
aboard, an official said.
   Firefighters used special equipment to pull the bodies from the
twisted metal of the elevator, which fell into the basement of
Bellvitge Hospital. The victims were visiting friends or relatives
at the hospital.
   The cause of the accident was not known, said hospital spokesman
Francesc Moreau. The Catalonian town where it occurred is near
Barcelona.
