<SECOND>AM-BRF--Alabama Chancellor,0116</SECOND>
<HEAD>New President for University of Alabama System</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUSCALOOSA, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Colorado State University President
Philip Austin was picked Sunday to be chancellor of the University
of Alabama system campuses at Tuscaloosa, Birmingham and Huntsville.
   Austin, who also served as chancellor of a university system
that includes the University of Southern Colorado at Pueblo and
Fort Lewis College, was elected unanimously by Alabama trustees
following a private, one-hour meeting.
   Austin, 47, said he plans to be at his new post before the start
of the fall semester.
   He succeeds Thomas Bartlett, who resigned as chancellor of the
39,000 student system in October to take a similar post in Oregon.
