<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A group of vengeful men waving baseball bats
beat a police officer's 17-year-old son and left him dying with a
bullet in his back, police said Sunday.
   A 19-year-old man, Rafael Droz of Philadelphia, was charged with
murder Sunday and police were searching for up to a dozen more
suspects, said homicide Lt. James Henwood.
   The attackers piled out of three cars Saturday night in North
Philadelphia and went after Sean Dailey and a group of nine to 15
