<HEAD>Fire Kills 14 in Manila</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fourteen people, including a
1-year-old girl, were killed when fire swept through a crowded
Manila neighborhood early Monday, police said.
   Lt. Honorato Manuel, chief of the Manila police arson division,
said the fire began in the stairs of an old two-story wooden house
in the Santa Ana district, where four families were renting rooms.
   Two of the families escaped through the back stairs but the
others were trapped in their rooms, which had iron bars in the
windows, Manuel said. Among those killed were seven children and a
70-year-old man, he added.
   ``Witnesses said the victims were waving and calling for help,
but neighbors could not go near because it was already very hot and
they did not know how to save the people trapped inside,'' Manuel
said.
   The fire lasted for 45 minutes and razed 10 houses, Manuel said.
